description.p:
From the data reported in Example 1 it can be inferred that:


Natrosol and, to a lesser extent, Magnafloc stimulate gas production and thus decay of vitamin C;


at neutral or even alkaline pH values gas production will be minimal;


heating of the samples to 65 (degree)  C. to facilitate dissolution of the viscosifyer leads to gas production and thus decay of vitamin C;


concentrated vitamin C solutions tend to form suspensions of (sodium)ascorbate upon increasing the pH value of the solutions to 7.
